 Hand-made oil-paper umbrellas are becoming popular again with millenials in China. Aside from their daily use, oil-paper umbrellas were often using on special occasions such as weddings, due to their pronunication being similar to the Cantonese for "having kids". Watch the video to see how to make an oil-paper umbrella. What a romantic art! Video credit to "Master of ancient umbrella (Jianglinfenghua)"（kuaishou#qingyu02）, posted on Chinese online video-sharing platform Kuaishou. (Source: Kuaishou) 